    "body": "Currently [`da.bincount` requires the input array be 1-D]( https://github.com/dask/dask/blob/2f308e72a46de818055819108429e8f7ce7ba03b/dask/array/routines.py#L529-L531 ). If the actual array is multidimensional, this requires the user to flatten the array first, which can be quite expensive. It would be preferable to relax this to a warning and simply handle `bincount` on all of the chunks as if the array were flattened already.",
